Senators Summers of the 13th, Hickman of the 4th, Echols of the 49th, Goodman of the 8th,
Watson of the 11th, and others offered the following amendment #1:
1 Amend HB 491 (LC 44 3109S) by inserting before "to provide for related matters;" on line
2 4 the following:
3 to extend the firearms, archery, and primitive weapons hunting seasons for deer;
4 By inserting between lines 20 and 21 the following:
5 SECTION 2.
6 Said article is further amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
7 "27-3-51.
8 Beginning on July 1, 2025, firearms, archery, and primitive weapons hunting seasons for
9 deer shall be extended as follows:
10 (1) Firearms: 14 additional days, at such dates as determined by the department;
11 (2) Archery: seven additional days, at such dates as determined by the department; and
12 (3) Primitive weapons: nine additional days, at such dates as determined by the
13 department."
14 By renumbering Sections 2 and 3 as Sections 3 and 4, respectively.
